	"description": "Managing state has always been a critical aspect of making web applications with\nReact. The most basic way to do this is prop drilling. In prop drilling, you\npass props around from the parent component to other components that need it, no\nmatter how deeply nested they are.\n\nThe problem with prop drilling is that, as the application grows in complexity,\npassing data through multiple levels of components can become messy, cumbersome,\nand error-prone.\n\nThe React Context API was released in 2018 to ",
